-- Market Chatter- Corporate finance press digest
-- 
-- Wed May 21, 2014 12:12AM EDT
-- None



May 21 (Reuters) - The following corporate finance-related stories were reported by media:

* The top foundation shareholder of Italy's Banca Carige <CRGI.MI> is placing a 15 percent stake in the lender in a range of 0.435 to 0.48 euros per share, a market source said on Tuesday. [ID:nL6N0O64ZR]  * State investor 1Malaysia Development Bhd (1MDB) has won a six-month extension on a 6.17 billion ringgit ($1.9 billion) bridge loan, giving it more time to launch a planned IPO of its power assets to cut the debt, people familiar with the matter said. [ID:nL3N0O70WG]  * Clayton, Dubilier & Rice LLC is in advanced talks to acquire wound care company Healogics Inc from private equity peer Metalmark Capital Holdings LLC for around $1 billion, according to people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL6N0O65R8]  * Private equity firm Warburg Pincus LLC is close to a deal to acquire Wencor Group LLC, a manufacturer of commercial aircraft parts, for between $800 million and $900 million, people familiar with the matter said on Tuesday. [ID:nL1N0O60X1]  * The private equity owner of Pro Mach Inc is exploring a sale of the packaging equipment maker that could value it at close to $1 billion, according to people familiar with the matter, the latest in a wave of such deals in the sector. [ID:nL6N0O5509]  * UK holiday-to-insurance firm Saga has covered the books for the 550 million pounds ($926.67 million) of new shares it is issuing in its London initial public offering, two sources familiar with the matter said on Tuesday. [ID:nL6N0O64NJ]  For the deals of the day click on [DEALS/]